        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 8:14PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 814 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Steens, or near Columbus, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vernon, Sulligent, Millport, Kennedy, Ethelsville, Blooming Grove,
Lamar County Airport, Bedford, Crossville, Cody, Lamar County Public
Lake, Shaw, Star, Forest, Hightogy, Macedonia, and Melborne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
